TASK_DESCRIPTION=The DB only supports 10 fields (title, status, type, description, assigned_to, team, tags, acceptance_criteria, current_phase, total_phases) but .task files use 37. The Task Reviewer pipeline is BLOCKED — it cannot write review_verdict, review_findings, review_timestamp. Add these columns to the tasks table in Go via migration or ALTER TABLE: review_verdict, review_findings, review_timestamp, plan_id, priority, notes, result, decision_log, subtasks, timestamps, blockers, related_files, attachments, dispatch_mode, created_by, owner, files, commits, summary, depends_on, merged_into, updated. Also update the valid-fields whitelist in the task update command handler so doey-ctl task update accepts all of them. Go source is in tui/cmd/doey-ctl/. P0 — blocking the review pipeline for task 149.
